  "instructions": [
    "Preheat a wood-fired oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "In a large mixing bowl, combine chorizo, onion, garlic, cilantro, parsley, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Mix well to combine.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a 9x13-inch baking dish lined with parchment paper.",
    "Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with grated cheddar cheese.",
    "Top with crushed crackers.",
    "Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and the filling is heated through.",
    "Remove from the oven and let cool for a few minutes before serving.",
    "Slice into 6-8 pieces and serve hot.",
    "Garnish with additional cilantro and parsley, if desired."
